# WebSocket

**This project is REST-only (Express HTTP). No WebSocket/SSE implementation exists.**

## Do not add unless requested

- `socket.io`, `ws`, Server-Sent Events infrastructure

## When realtime is needed

- Authenticate socket connection with same JWT + session validation
- Authorize per-room/per-resource
- Rate limit connection and message events
- Use separate namespace from REST error handling

## Current alternative

Clients poll REST endpoints or use frontend refresh (`resource.reload()` in Angular).

Do not introduce WebSocket dependencies without explicit user request.
